social_posts.post_text: Im always amazed how close New York is to DC….when there’s no traffic. But it’s always a fun getaway especially around the holiday season. No matter how many times I’ve been there is always something new to see and experience

Looking forward to taking many more steps together with you….and a stroller!

I should probably buy some Hokas so I can be the taller one
Chloe Elizabeth Cruz 💕 Born February 28 at 9:47AM • 6lbs 1oz • 19.25 inches long • lots of dark hair like dad! 🥰
4 days old 🤍

One month with our sweet Chloe girl - we have no idea where time has gone! She loves to snuggle, is very animated and vocal, a bit of a night owl, and has mommy’s big appetite! She’s exactly 2lbs above her birth weight and can finally fit in her newborn clothes! 🤍
Hoppy Easter!! 🐰🐣
Thanks to @mckinziejeffersonphoto for capturing so many amazing shots of our little family for Chloe’s newborn shoot! Here are a few faves 👨‍👩‍👧💕
Happy First Mothers Day to @alohaannieee !! Thanks for everything you do and for not getting too mad when I forget to log a diaper!

HAPPY 14th BIRTHDAY, KIRBY! 🎂🎈Just two weeks ago we were unsure if this was a milestone we were going to be able to celebrate. On April 28, he had life-saving emergency surgery to remove a tumor on his spleen that ruptured. Recovery hasn’t been all smooth sailing, but he’s getting better each day. Thank you so much to everyone who has continued to check in on him — it means so much to us. 

The preliminary pathology report of his biopsy shows NO SIGNS of cancer! There was less than a 30% chance of the tumor being benign, so we couldn’t be happier! Kirby truly is beating the odds! We hope the final report shares the same findings.

Regardless, we will continue to celebrate every single day we have with our sweet, quirky boy. We love you Kirby, our first born baby! ♥️

Chloe gets super excited for food these days. Actually eating it is a another story

Soaking in the last weekend of the summer season before we all have to go back to work and school. At least the weather and sunset is nice in Old Town.
I cant believe it’s October already. We spent this hot fall Sunday picking up some pumpkins 🎃 at Nails Produce.

Now with a child of our own we can now go to fun kiddie events and not feel like the awkward adults. Too bad Chloe isn’t old enough to enjoy all the slides at Cox farms. We’d definitely go back next year when Chloe can enjoy all the kiddie activities and slides.🛝
